pageContext.claim: Graham-Cassidy bill: "It's also great for Maine; it's also great for Alaska. Every state you're talking about, it happens to be particularly good for. So I don't know what they're doing. But you know what? Eventually, we'll win, whether it's now or later.‚Äù
pageContext.analysis: While Graham-Cassidy bill had carve-outs for Alaska and Maine, the states would still have lost federal funding. Sen. Lisa Murkowski (R-Ala.) and Sen. Susan Collins (R-Me.) were not supportive of the measure.
